properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 15 at 7:10PM MST until January 18 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 40 to 50 mph with gusts up to 70 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County, North
Snowy Range Foothills, South Laramie Range and South Laramie
Range Foothills. This includes Interstate 80 near Arlington and
Elk mountain as well as I-25 at Bordeaux and the I-80 Summit.

* WHEN...From early Friday morning through early Saturday
morning.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Travel could be difficult,
especially for high profile vehicles with strong crosswinds. Use
caution if you are driving. Secure loose outdoor items as they
may be blown and damaged.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM EARLY FRIDAY MORNING THROUGH SATURDAY EARLY MORNING
